      "en": "An event of typeXRInputSourceEventwhich gets sent to the session object when one of its input devices finishes its primary action or gets disconnected while in the process of handling a primary action. For example: for button or trigger actions, this means the button has been released; for spoken commands, it means the user has finished speaking. This is the last of the threeselect*events to be sent. Also available through theonselectendevent handler property."
